ions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Hiltgund was born in 1180, in Bavaria, her father, Hiltgund, was 27 and her mother, von Bavaria, was 25. She married Chuonrad Von Fend I in 1210, in Bavaria, Germany. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1240, in her hometown, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1180–1240":"1180–1240","1175–1229":"1175–1229","1210–1260":"1210–1260","1222–1285":"1222–1285","1154–Male":"1154–Surnud","1156–Female":"1156–Surnud","nach 1229":"pärast 1229","1154":"1154","1285":"1285","1175":"1175","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","1180":"1180","UM 1180":"umbes 1180","1156":"1156","1222":"1222","1210":"1210","about 1222":"umbes 1222","after 1210":"pärast 1210","1229":"1229","Augsburg, Augsburg, Bayern, Deutschland":"Augsburg, Augsburg, Bayern, Saksamaa","Augsburg, Bavaria, Germany":"Landkreis Augsburg, Bayern, Saksamaa","Bavaria, Bayern, Germany":"Bayern, Saksamaa","Bavaria, Holy Roman Empire":"Königreich Bayern"},"fi":{"1180–1240":"1180–1240","1175–1229":"1175–1229","1210–1260":"1210–1260","1222–1285":"1222–1285","1154–Male":"1154–Kuollut","1156–Female":"1156–Kuollut","nach 1229":"1229 jälkeen","1154":"1154","1285":"1285","1175":"1175","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","1180":"1180","UM 1180":"noin 1180","1156":"1156","1222":"1222","1210":"1210","about 1222":"noin 1222","after 1210":"1210 jälkeen","1229":"1229","Augsburg, Augsburg, Bayern, Deutschland":"Augsburg, Augsburg, Bayern, Saksa","Augsburg, Bavaria, Germany":